               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370918-name-1208" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1208" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1208" type="surname" value="MARSH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1208" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>SARAH MARSH</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of Joseph Marsh, and live in Drogmore-lane Streatham, surrey. I had an ass safe on the 18th of August in my yard—it was turned out about half-past eight o'clock., on Thursday, for feeding in the land—I have seen it since—it was found at Lewisham by the constable—the Magistrate at Greenwich gave it me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370918-name-1209" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1209" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1209" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1209" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS SMITH</persName>
                  </hi>. I went after the ass, and found it at the house of Mr. Perren, near Lewisham-bridge—the prisoner's house is nearly</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183709180188"></xptr>
               <p>opposite—I went with the constable and asked him about it—he said he had sold Mr. Perren the ass, and had changed it for another donkey and a shilling.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370918-name-1210" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1210" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1210" type="surname" value="PERREN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1210" type="given" value="ABRAHAM"></interp>ABRAHAM PERREN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a donkey driver—I bought the donkey of the prisoner on the 18th of August—I gave him another one for it and a shilling.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence</hi>. I bought that donkey on the 18th of August between Lewisham and Sydenham, of Thomas Martin, a man with a sear on his left cheek—I gave him 15<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. and a pot of half and half for it—it was not big enough for me, and I sold it to Mr. Perren—the Magistrate's clerk said that he knew Martin—that he was a noted donkey stealer, but we could not find him.</p>
